<br>
If someone kills someone else in prison that is a faliure of the prison system.<br>
<br>
According to that argument all people convicted of a crime should be put to death, so that they might never commit another crime.<br>
<br>
Ther are innocent people in jail - there are criminals that get out of jail and never commit another crime - that doesn't make it valid to say that all criminals should be let go either.<br>
<br>
Deterance is not the prevention of people commiting the same crime again - it is preventing someone from commiting the crime in the first place.<br>
<br>
It doesn't take alot of thought to realise that if people thought they would be caught that they would still commit the crime.  People do not think they will be caught - thus the punishment doesn't matter.<br>
<br>
Do you think that public decapitation or hangings prevented crime back when they happened?  People still commited crime then - they do now.<br>
<br>
